\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. longipes} (Boiss. & Heldr.) A. Cheval.,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  83}: 641 (1937) ({\i Linaria cymbalaria} subsp.{\i  longipes} (Boiss. & Heldr.) Hayek). Like {\b 1}(a) but leaves not more than 15 × 20 mm; spur of corolla 4-5 mm, much longer than calyx; capsule 3-4 mm, minutely glandular-puberulent; seeds of each loculus concrescent when ripe, forming a coarsely alveolate and irregularly winged mass c. 3 × 2 mm.{\i  Rocky or stony places by the sea. S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr. ({\i E. Mediterranean region.})
\par

