\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. C. pilosa} (Jacq.) L. H. Bailey,{\i  Gentes Herb.}{\b  1}: 136 (1923). Stems and leaves villous. Stems up to 35 cm; middle and upper internodes about equal. Leaves usually c. 10 × 12 mm, alternate reniform, with (5-)7(-11) rounded or mucronate, subequal lobes. Pedicel at anthesis about equalling subtending petiole, elongating considerably in fruit. Calyx c. 2 mm, villous. Corolla 10-12 mm, pale lilac to white; spur c. 1 mm. Capsule pubescent, exceeding calyx. Seeds 0·6-0·8 mm, brown, subglobose, rather finely rugose.
